\pard\f0\fs28 {\b  T. conspersus} var.{\b  lycaonicus} Celak., {\i Flora} ({\i Regensb}.){\b  66}: 156 (1883) ({\i T. zygioides} var.{\i  lycaonicus} (Celak.) Ronniger), from the E. Aegean region, may represent a subspecies of {\b 44}. It differs in having leaves usually 10-12 × 1-1·5 mm, sparsely hairy, and calyx 3·5-4·5 mm, with upper teeth up to 1·2 mm. It has been recorded from Turkey-in-Europe (near Gelibolu), and intermediates are found in Bulgaria.
