\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 46. T. herba-barona} Loisel.,{\i  Fl. Gall.} 360 (1807). Branches procumbent to ascending, woody; long, creeping, non-flowering branches absent. Flowering stems 5-10 cm, hairy all round. Leaves usually 6-9 × 2-4 mm, elliptical to rhombic-ovate, petiolate, acute, herbaceous, with flat to subrevolute margins, glabrous or puberulent, ciliate at base; veins indistinct. Inflorescence subcapitate, lax, sometimes with the lower verticillasters remote. Bracts similar to the leaves. Calyx 3-5 mm; upper teeth up to 1·5 mm, somewhat longer than wide, scabrid, not ciliate. Corolla up to 9 mm, pale purple. 2n = 56. •{\i  Corse, Sardegna.} Co Sa.
